<br>
get parried.<br>
hit<br>
get parried<br>
get blocked<br>
get parried<br>
get parried<br>
get parried<br>
get shield slammed.<br>
<br>
i have my 2.8 1h hammer out so i get in a lot of futile attacks instead of the few i normally would have.<br>
<br>
i purge the slam and IP for 1100 or so of my 1432 hits.<br>
<br>
at this point i run around the corner since a wizard is coming down the stairs, he bolts me twice for about 550 total.  the paladin slams the shadowblade, i mez the paladin to get him off the SB and then attack the wizard.<br>
<br>
SB gets out of range but paladin is chasing since he purged, so i attack the wizard and he runs after the paladin who is chasing the SB.  through the arch into the room between the alb stiars and the alb side merchants.  i do about 40% damage to the wizard since i'm out of endurance, i think he's grouped with the paladin as he seems to be enjoying a long sprint time.<br>
<br>
in any case the shadowblade runs over onto the little ledge on the left and jumps off since he's safe from fall damage.  i die on the little ledge shortly thereafter still trying to kill the wizard.  the SB misses his second well lined up perf, and then chases the wizard around and eventually is killed.<br>
<br>
in the entire fight we (rank 7 skald and rank 5 shadowblade) didn't manage to do more than 25% damage to the paladin.<br>
<br>
good game mythic.  thanks for blindly refusing to give us shield spec and 2.0.  or any defense of ANY sort for that matter.  we really appreciate being a second rate class.<br>
<br>
there is absolutely NO justification for not giving skalds shield spec.  none.  other than incomprehensible stubborness on the part of mythic. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.paradoxguild.com/images/phlsig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elvana@teamskald>Elvana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/25/03 10:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=710.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why are paladins so much bette than skalds?</span><hr size=1> There is some justification in it... <br>
